{"kind": "section", "id": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/tools-reference.md#overview", "page_url": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/tools-reference.md", "anchor": "overview", "breadcrumb": "Tools reference > Overview", "level": 2, "position": 0, "text": "> Complete reference for the tools Claude Code can use, including permission requirements.\n\nClaude Code has access to a set of built-in tools that help it understand and modify your codebase. The tool names are the exact strings you use in permission rules, subagent tool lists, and hook matchers. To disable a tool entirely, add its name to the `deny` array in your permission settings.\n\nTo add custom tools, connect an MCP server. To extend Claude with reusable prompt-based workflows, write a skill, which runs through the existing `Skill` tool rather than adding a new tool entry.\n\nPermission rules can be configured using `/permissions` or in permission settings. Also see Tool-specific permission rules.", "synthesized": false, "parent_section_id": null, "external_links": []}
{"kind": "link", "section_id": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/tools-reference.md#bash-tool-behavior", "href": "/en/permissions#working-directories", "text": "additional working directory", "is_internal": true, "is_anchor_only": false, "source_kind": "prose"}
{"kind": "link", "section_id": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/tools-reference.md#bash-tool-behavior", "href": "/en/env-vars", "text": "`CLAUDE_ENV_FILE`", "is_internal": true, "is_anchor_only": false, "source_kind": "prose"}
{"kind": "link", "section_id": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/tools-reference.md#bash-tool-behavior", "href": "/en/hooks#persist-environment-variables", "text": "SessionStart hook", "is_internal": true, "is_anchor_only": false, "source_kind": "prose"}
{"kind": "section", "id": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/tools-reference.md#bash-tool-behavior", "page_url": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/tools-reference.md", "anchor": "bash-tool-behavior", "breadcrumb": "Tools reference > Bash tool behavior", "level": 2, "position": 1, "text": "The Bash tool runs each command in a separate process with the following persistence behavior:\n\n- When Claude runs `cd` in the main session, the new working directory carries over to later Bash commands as long as it stays inside the project directory or an additional working directory you added with `--add-dir`, `/add-dir`, or `additionalDirectories` in settings. Subagent sessions never carry over working directory changes.\n  - If `cd` lands outside those directories, Claude Code resets to the project directory and appends `Shell cwd was reset to <dir>` to the tool result.\n  - To disable this carry-over so every Bash command starts in the project directory, set `CLAUDE_BASH_MAINTAIN_PROJECT_WORKING_DIR=1`.\n- Environment variables do not persist. An `export` in one command will not be available in the next.\n\nActivate your virtualenv or conda environment before launching Claude Code. To make environment variables persist across Bash commands, set `CLAUDE_ENV_FILE` to a shell script before launching Claude Code, or use a SessionStart hook to populate it dynamically.", "synthesized": false, "parent_section_id": null, "external_links": []}
{"kind": "link", "section_id": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/tools-reference.md#lsp-tool-behavior", "href": "/en/discover-plugins#code-intelligence", "text": "code intelligence plugin", "is_internal": true, "is_anchor_only": false, "source_kind": "prose"}
{"kind": "section", "id": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/tools-reference.md#lsp-tool-behavior", "page_url": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/tools-reference.md", "anchor": "lsp-tool-behavior", "breadcrumb": "Tools reference > LSP tool behavior", "level": 2, "position": 2, "text": "The LSP tool gives Claude code intelligence from a running language server. After each file edit, it automatically reports type errors and warnings so Claude can fix issues without a separate build step. Claude can also call it directly to navigate code:\n\n- Jump to a symbol's definition\n- Find all references to a symbol\n- Get type information at a position\n- List symbols in a file or workspace\n- Find implementations of an interface\n- Trace call hierarchies\n\nThe tool is inactive until you install a code intelligence plugin for your language. The plugin bundles the language server configuration, and you install the server binary separately.", "synthesized": false, "parent_section_id": null, "external_links": []}
{"kind": "callout", "id": "c51fe49c229a6470", "section_id": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/tools-reference.md#monitor-tool", "position": 0, "callout_kind": "note", "text": "The Monitor tool requires Claude Code v2.1.98 or later."}
{"kind": "link", "section_id": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/tools-reference.md#monitor-tool", "href": "/en/permissions#tool-specific-permission-rules", "text": "permission rules as Bash", "is_internal": true, "is_anchor_only": false, "source_kind": "prose"}
{"kind": "link", "section_id": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/tools-reference.md#monitor-tool", "href": "/en/plugins-reference#monitors", "text": "plugin monitors", "is_internal": true, "is_anchor_only": false, "source_kind": "prose"}
{"kind": "section", "id": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/tools-reference.md#monitor-tool", "page_url": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/tools-reference.md", "anchor": "monitor-tool", "breadcrumb": "Tools reference > Monitor tool", "level": 2, "position": 3, "text": "The Monitor tool lets Claude watch something in the background and react when it changes, without pausing the conversation. Ask Claude to:\n\n- Tail a log file and flag errors as they appear\n- Poll a PR or CI job and report when its status changes\n- Watch a directory for file changes\n- Track output from any long-running script you point it at\n\nClaude writes a small script for the watch, runs it in the background, and receives each output line as it arrives. You keep working in the same session and Claude interjects when an event lands. Stop a monitor by asking Claude to cancel it or by ending the session.\n\nMonitor uses the same permission rules as Bash, so `allow` and `deny` patterns you have set for Bash apply here too. It is not available on Amazon Bedrock, Google Vertex AI, or Microsoft Foundry. It is also not available when `DISABLE_TELEMETRY` or `CLAUDE_CODE_DISABLE_NONESSENTIAL_TRAFFIC` is set.\n\nPlugins can declare monitors that start automatically when the plugin is active, instead of asking Claude to start them. See plugin monitors.", "synthesized": false, "parent_section_id": null, "external_links": []}
{"kind": "codeblock", "id": "5153c18930ac6303", "section_id": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/tools-reference.md#enable-the-powershell-tool", "position": 0, "language": "json", "text": "{\n  \"env\": {\n    \"CLAUDE_CODE_USE_POWERSHELL_TOOL\": \"1\"\n  }\n}", "preceding_paragraph": "Set `CLAUDE_CODE_USE_POWERSHELL_TOOL=1` in your environment or in `settings.json`:", "in_codegroup": false, "codegroup_id": null}
{"kind": "section", "id": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/tools-reference.md#enable-the-powershell-tool", "page_url": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/tools-reference.md", "anchor": "enable-the-powershell-tool", "breadcrumb": "Tools reference > PowerShell tool > Enable the PowerShell tool", "level": 3, "position": 5, "text": "Set `CLAUDE_CODE_USE_POWERSHELL_TOOL=1` in your environment or in `settings.json`:\n\nOn Windows, set the variable to `0` to opt out of the rollout. On Linux, macOS, and WSL, the tool requires PowerShell 7 or later: install `pwsh` and ensure it is on your `PATH`.\n\nOn Windows, Claude Code auto-detects `pwsh.exe` for PowerShell 7+ with a fallback to `powershell.exe` for PowerShell 5.1. The Bash tool remains registered alongside the PowerShell tool, so you may need to ask Claude to use PowerShell.", "synthesized": false, "parent_section_id": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/tools-reference.md#powershell-tool", "external_links": []}
