{"kind": "section", "id": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/tools-reference.md#shell-selection-in-settings-hooks-and-skills", "page_url": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/tools-reference.md", "anchor": "shell-selection-in-settings-hooks-and-skills", "breadcrumb": "Tools reference > PowerShell tool > Shell selection in settings, hooks, and skills", "level": 3, "position": 6, "text": "Three additional settings control where PowerShell is used:\n\n- `\"defaultShell\": \"powershell\"` in `settings.json`: routes interactive `!` commands through PowerShell. Requires the PowerShell tool to be enabled.\n- `\"shell\": \"powershell\"` on individual command hooks: runs that hook in PowerShell. Hooks spawn PowerShell directly, so this works regardless of `CLAUDE_CODE_USE_POWERSHELL_TOOL`.\n- `shell: powershell` in skill frontmatter: runs `!`command`` blocks in PowerShell. Requires the PowerShell tool to be enabled.\n\nThe same main-session working-directory reset behavior described under the Bash tool section applies to PowerShell commands, including the `CLAUDE_BASH_MAINTAIN_PROJECT_WORKING_DIR` environment variable.", "synthesized": false, "parent_section_id": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/tools-reference.md#powershell-tool", "external_links": []}
{"kind": "section", "id": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/tools-reference.md#preview-limitations", "page_url": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/tools-reference.md", "anchor": "preview-limitations", "breadcrumb": "Tools reference > PowerShell tool > Preview limitations", "level": 3, "position": 7, "text": "The PowerShell tool has the following known limitations during the preview:\n\n- PowerShell profiles are not loaded\n- On Windows, sandboxing is not supported", "synthesized": false, "parent_section_id": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/tools-reference.md#powershell-tool", "external_links": []}
{"kind": "section", "id": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/tools-reference.md#powershell-tool", "page_url": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/tools-reference.md", "anchor": "powershell-tool", "breadcrumb": "Tools reference > PowerShell tool", "level": 2, "position": 4, "text": "The PowerShell tool lets Claude run PowerShell commands natively. On Windows, this means commands run in PowerShell instead of routing through Git Bash. On Windows without Git Bash, the tool is enabled automatically. On Windows with Git Bash installed, the tool is rolling out progressively. On Linux, macOS, and WSL, the tool is opt-in.", "synthesized": false, "parent_section_id": null, "external_links": []}
{"kind": "codeblock", "id": "0329dbcc8f0476e8", "section_id": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/tools-reference.md#check-which-tools-are-available", "position": 0, "language": "text", "text": "What tools do you have access to?", "preceding_paragraph": "Your exact tool set depends on your provider, platform, and settings. To check what's loaded in a running session, ask Claude directly:", "in_codegroup": false, "codegroup_id": null}
{"kind": "section", "id": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/tools-reference.md#check-which-tools-are-available", "page_url": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/tools-reference.md", "anchor": "check-which-tools-are-available", "breadcrumb": "Tools reference > Check which tools are available", "level": 2, "position": 8, "text": "Your exact tool set depends on your provider, platform, and settings. To check what's loaded in a running session, ask Claude directly:\n\nClaude gives a conversational summary. For exact MCP tool names, run `/mcp`.", "synthesized": false, "parent_section_id": null, "external_links": []}
